What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Major needs work. Capstone projects need work. My project was saved by a great professor and some cool classmates.
The capstones are a sad, sad state of affairs for the Jackson Institute and Yale. I enjoyed my experience in spite of this fact, thanks to a great team and a great facilitator.
It's interesting as a senior project. I think there are many positives but the experimental nature of it bothers me.
